So, I will just throw in a possible idea (which doesn't mean it is feasible or even it's my favorite idea to improve skalds) to provoke a discussion.<br>
Well ... why not breaking the skald taboo : instruments.<br>
<br>
Whooops, I said the I... word ! Bad Kjeld ! But don't freak out yet, here's the reasoning.<br>
<br>
Facts and assumptions<br>
- The skald lags somewhat behind the other speed classes (with the upcoming minstrel patch)<br>
- However skalds have an advantage over the others two : he doesn't need instrument swapping, which means he can fully use his powers and fight at the same time.<br>
- One of the age old arguments that the player base commonly oppose to skald's plea for improvment is that the lack of instruments balances the superior abilities of bards and minstrels (&quot;I'll gladly give you my AE mez if you take my drum too ...&quot;)<br>
- It's pretty obvious that the skald community is strongly against the introduction of instruments for skalds, and many actually chose the class because of this independance from instruments<br>
- Horns look cool<br>
- Skalds are useless in keep defenses<br>
- Skald support is weak, multiple skalds don't stack, battlesong at 50 suck, even with the improved song of rest<br>
<br>
So what is my idea that will hopefully take all of those factors into account ?<br>
Add the Horn instrument for skalds. He will be required for the use of three additional song in the skald's repertoite.<br>
- Horn of War : a castable (not shout) 1500 range direct damage, similar to Thane's, which primary usage should be keep battles (or milegate standoffs)<br>
- Horn of Valhalla : a powerful horn blow, castable (not shout) PBAE damage spell, with realtively low damage and hefty cost (similar to Thane's, without a timer but with a casting time), which primary usage should be keep battles.<br>
- Rally Horn : a secondary &quot;support&quot; spell of your choice, haste, endurance or whatever, that will be a second choice to damage add if a second skald is in a group and if he chooses so, depending on his spec (make it so the level 50 BS is valuable here) and the composition of the group (the alternative beeing &quot;normal&quot; melee play)<br>
<br>
So how many birds do we kill with that stone ?<br>
- We introduce new skald abilities, with the &quot;politically correct&quot; drawback of using an instrument, which balances the power of the new abilities, and help &quot;justify&quot; a skald boost compared to the other music classes<br>
- *Nothing is touched, nothing changes to the way we played our skalds already* We still, in normal circumstances, play as usual, with our sword and shouts. The instrument doesn't interfere with the way the skald is played essentially<br>
- The skald will normally only use the instrument in occasion where he was previously useless anyway (keeps) or wouldn't make a difference (some exp groups ...)<br>
- The instrument is only here to make sure that the new abilities are ONLY used for their intended usage : ie the DD and PB spell, due to the instrument and cast time restricitions, will be impossible to use in standard engagments to improve skald's &quot;anytime&quot; damage output.<br>
- Fluff is cool <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So ? What do you think about this idea ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/18/03 10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A wild idea : breaking a taboo</span><hr size=1> I long thought about the idea of having new songs based on instruments.  The only real difference between your idea and what I was thinking was that I wanted us to have a 1-handed horn that could be held in the shield slot, allowing us to battle with a 1H weapon at the same time.  A new set of songs which would be introduced to support this new instrument would give skalds the option of 1H and these songs or 2 hand and the original (although still tweaked) songs.<br>
